Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of protocol standards for deterministic properties on Ethernet based packet-switched networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also focuses on the management and control of scheduled traffic streams with periodic properties, which is related to system design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a likely sub-category as well. The use of gate control lists and entries for ultra-low latency and zero packet loss also involves information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the effects of using the IEEE 802.1Qcc management protocol on a typical industrial control network, which is related to distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper examines the effects of using a centralized network/distributed user model and a fully-distributed model, which involves software engineering and programming, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category.
